                            <comment id="485132" author="sebastien" created="Fri, 23 Jan 2026 10:29:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Wow, in this case ti would be related to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19732&quot; title=&quot;sanity-lfsck test_18a: FAIL: (6.1) Expect 3 fixed on mds1, but got: 248&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19732&quot;&gt;LU-19732&lt;/a&gt;, for which Hongchao pushed patch &quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19732&quot; title=&quot;sanity-lfsck test_18a: FAIL: (6.1) Expect 3 fixed on mds1, but got: 248&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19732&quot;&gt;LU-19732&lt;/a&gt; ldiskfs: keep RHEL10.x not to update cmtime&quot; at &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/63529&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/63529&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="485130" author="qian_wc" created="Fri, 23 Jan 2026 10:16:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;After analyze, I think I found the root reason for cmtime failures.&lt;br/&gt;
It is the stale ext4-nocatime.patch:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;static&lt;/span&gt; inline struct timespec64 ext4_current_time(struct inode *inode)
+{
+	&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (IS_NOCMTIME(inode))
+		&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; inode_get_ctime(inode);
+	&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; current_time(inode);
+}
+#define current_time(a) ext4_current_time(a)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The newer kernel EXT4 FS module does not use current_time to set amtime with the current time any more. Instead it is using inode_set_ctime_current(). This function will be used to update ctime or atime in ext4_xattr_set_handle().&lt;br/&gt;
We need to update the ldiskfs patch for ext4-nocatime.patch to support newer kernel S_NOCMTIME for XATTR SET.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19729&quot; title=&quot;sanity test_160l: FAIL: MTIME changelog not recorded&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19729&quot;&gt;LU-19729&lt;/a&gt; should also be related to this bug.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="484747" author="sebastien" created="Wed, 21 Jan 2026 07:24:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Contrary to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19729&quot; title=&quot;sanity test_160l: FAIL: MTIME changelog not recorded&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19729&quot;&gt;LU-19729&lt;/a&gt;, this specific issue &quot;FAIL: release changed ctime from xx to yy&quot; on sanity-hsm test_24a only occurred when testing on RHEL10, so it looks specific to this distro.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
